"""
Information Sharding Experiment: Period 1 Action Prediction
============================================================

Tests whether information asymmetry increases prediction diversity and
improves ensemble performance.

Conditions:
- Baseline: Generic, 100% information (N=100)
- Sharding: Generic, mixed information (N=100: 20@25%, 20@50%, 20@75%, 40@100%)

Hypothesis: Ensemble with sharded information outperforms uniform full information
due to increased diversity without excessive noise.
"""

